			    STPJS 344</div>
  <p class="cont">time henceforth occupy your attention. The Scriptures inform us that &ldquo;This is life eternal that they
  might know thee, the only true God, and Jesus Christ whom thou hast sent.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">1</span></p>
  <p class="std">If any man does not know God,<span class="footRef">2</span> and inquires what kind of a being he is,&mdash;if he will search
  diligently his own heart<span class="footRef">3</span>&mdash;if the declaration of Jesus and the apostles be true, he will realize that he
  has not eternal life;<span class="footRef">4</span> for there can be eternal life on no other principle.</p>
  <p class="std">My first object is to find out the character of the only wise and true God,<span class="footRef">5</span> and what kind of a
  being he is; and if I am so fortunate as to be the man to comprehend God,<span class="footRef">6</span> and explain or convey
  the principles to your hearts, so that the Spirit seals<span class="footRef">7</span> them upon you, then let every man and woman
  henceforth sit in silence,<span class="footRef">8</span> put their hands on their mouths,<span class="footRef">9</span> and never lift their hands<span class="footRef">10</span> or voices,<span class="footRef">11</span>
  or say anything against the man of God<span class="footRef">12</span> or the servants of God<span class="footRef">13</span> again. But if I fail to do it, it
  becomes my duty to renounce all further pretensions to revelations and inspirations, or to be a
  prophet; and I should be like the rest of the world&mdash;a false teacher,<span class="footRef">14</span> be hailed as a friend, and no
  man would seek my life.<span class="footRef">15</span> But if all religious teachers were honest enough to renounce their
  pretensions to godliness<span class="footRef">16</span> when their ignorance of the knowledge of God is made manifest,<span class="footRef">17</span> they
  will all be as badly off as I am, at any rate; and you might as well take the lives of other false
  teachers as that of mine, if I am false. If any man is authorized to take away my life because he
  thinks and says I am a false teacher, then, upon the same principle, we should be justified in taking
  away the life of every false teacher, and where would be the end of blood? And who would not be
  the sufferer?<span class="textFootRef">a</span></p>
  <div class="topic">The Privilege of Religious Freedom</div>
  <p class="std">But meddle not<span class="footRef">18</span> with any man for his religion:<span class="footRef">19</span> and all governments ought to permit every
  man to enjoy his religion unmolested.<span class="footRef">20</span> No man is authorized to take away life in consequence of
  difference of religion, which all laws and governments ought to tolerate and protect, right or wrong.
  Every man has a natural, and, in our country, a constitutional right to be a false prophet,<span class="footRef">21</span> as well
  as a true prophet. If I show, verily, that</p>
